GET - Used to get a resource from server - idempotent
POST - For creating a resource on server/ sending data to server
PUT - Update a entire resource on server,
DELETE - Delete a resource from server
An HTTP method is idempotent if the intended effect on the server of
making a single request is the same as the effect of making several
GET is an idempotent method because it is only a read operation
and doesn't cause any state change in the backend.
